<TITLE>
What's New With Netperf
</TITLE>
<P>
<H1>
What's New With Netperf
</H1>  
<P>
Checking this area from time to time will tell you what is new with
the netperf benchmark. Announcements of new versions, and what has
changed, as well as other interesting netperf news can be found here.
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<hr>
<P>
<H2>The latest stable revision of netperf2 is 
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.netperf.org/netperf/netperf-2.4.1.tar.gz">
2.4.1
</A>
</H2>
</P>

<H2>
October 18, 2005
</H2>
Netperf.org has moved to a new system.  This has enabled a multitude
of changes:

A new <A HREF="ftp://ftp.netperf.org/netperf/">FTP download</A> location,
<A HREF="http://www.netperf.org/svn/netperf2"> subversion</A> repository,
and a new mailing list
<A HREF="http://www.netperf.org/pipermail/netperf-talk/">archive</A>.

<H2>
March 17, 2005 - netperf is now using a configure script, has merged
IPv4 and IPv6 tests and a host of other changes.  See the release notes
file for more.
</H2>

<H2>
The netperf benchmark includes support for OpenVMS, and support for Linux
sendfile().
</H2>
<P>
February 14, 2003 - Netperf now includes evolving support for OpenVMS and
support for the Linux flavor of sendfile().  Additionally, fixes to set 
SO_REUSEADDR on the netserver listen socket, fixes for IPv6, and other
sundries are included.
</P>
<H2>
The netperf benchmark includes the TCP_MAERTS test and IPv6
</H2>
<P>
July 11, 2002 - Netperf now includes a TCP_MAERTS test that has data 
flowing from the netserver to the netperf - this is opposite of the
classic TCP_STREAM test. In theory, IPv6 support is integrated :) 
Also -DUSE_KSTAT for Solaris CPU util, and -DUSE_PROC_STAT for Linux.
</P>
<H2>
The netperf-talk mailing list now has an online archive
</H2>
<P>
March 12, 1996 - The netperf-talk mailing list now has an online
<A HREF="/netperf/training/netperf-talk/index.html">
archive
</A>
of discussions in netperf-talk. This archive will update in
near real-time. More information can be found in the
<A HREF="/netperf/training/netperf-talk/netperf-talk-archive.html">
discription
</A>
of the archive.

<H2>Netperf 2.1 is Released</H2>
<P>
February 15, 1995 - Thanks to the assistance of many folks on the net,
revision 2.1 of netperf has released. A copy of the Release_Notes can
be found in the new netperf-talk
<A HREF="/netperf/training/netperf-talk/index.html">
archive
</A>
.
</P>
<HR>

